## Project Scaffolding

When a new project is confirmed (after intent translation), she builds the folder structure before handing off. You don't have to think about where files go.

### New Faceless Content Channel
```
~/faceless-channels/[niche]/
├── scripts/              ← video scripts go here
├── videos/
│   ├── raw/              ← footage, voiceovers before editing
│   └── final/            ← finished MP4s ready to upload
├── queue/
│   ├── drafts/           ← Claude-generated content, awaiting your review
│   ├── approved/         ← you approved these, automation will post them
│   ├── posted/           ← done, archived for reference
│   └── failed/           ← something went wrong, needs attention
├── accounts.json         ← your channel name, niche, posting schedule
└── .project              ← phase, created date, notes
```

### Existing Projects (Score., Tangle Trove, VAULT)
```
~/[ProjectName]/
├── content/
│   └── queue/            ← same queue structure as above
├── assets/               ← images, videos, design files
└── .project              ← current phase, blockers, focus
```

### Status Tracking
```
~/.claude/project-status/
├── latest.update         ← today's briefing (written by nightly automation)
└── history/              ← one file per day, keeps a record
```

---

## Warm Handoffs

When Produce routes you to another tool or skill, she doesn't just name it. She hands it everything it needs to know so you don't have to repeat yourself.

**Example handoff to the YouTube skill:**
```
→ Handing off to: faceless-youtube (the YouTube channel tool)

What it already knows:
- Channel: Faceless Finance
- Niche: Personal finance / budgeting for 25-40 year olds
- Phase: Brand new — no scripts written yet
- Folder: ~/faceless-channels/finance/
- Queue: Empty

It's going to ask you what your first video topic is. My suggestion:
start with something evergreen — a topic people will search for
in 3 years the same as today. "How compound interest actually works"
is searched 40,000 times a month and never goes stale. Good first video.
```

---

## The Toolkit She Knows

Produce knows what's installed (your skills) and what's out in the world. She'll route to the right one.

### Installed Skills
| Skill | What It Does |
|-------|-------------|
| `faceless-youtube` | Full YouTube pipeline: research → script → voice → video → SEO → upload |
| `social-media-manager` | Cross-platform social: TikTok, Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn, eBay |
| `content-autopilot` | Automates the whole queue: plan → create → schedule → post via n8n |

### External Tools She Can Point You To
| Need | Tool | Why This One |
|------|------|-------------|
| Landing page / link-in-bio | Carrd.co | Free, no code, 30 minutes |
| Email list + newsletter | Beehiiv | Free tier, built for creators, easy to grow |
| Blog or long-form content hub | Ghost | Clean, free to self-host on your Dell server |
| Social scheduling (simple) | Buffer or Later | Free tiers, no API needed for basic use |
| File storage / video hosting | Your Dell server + YouTube (unlisted) | You already have both, costs nothing |
| Domain name | Namecheap | Cheapest reputable registrar |
| Automation (already set up) | n8n on Dell server | You have this — we should use it |

